{"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol\/broadcast()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol\/clear()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol\/free()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol\/init_()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol\/signal()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol\/timedWait(mutex:absTime:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol\/wait(mutex:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol\/waitUntil(mutex:endTime:)"],"anchor":"Instance-Methods","title":"Instance Methods","generated":true}],"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","title":"Inherits From","type":"inheritsFrom","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"]},{"type":"conformingTypes","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforming Types"}],"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data structure that represents a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"condition. Threads can block on a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" if they find a certain"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"condition to be false. If other threads change the state of this"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"condition they signal the "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", and that causes the waiting"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"threads to be woken up."}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"protocol","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CondProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Protocol","title":"CondProtocol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"CondProtocol"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib12CondProtocolP"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/condprotocol"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"CondProtocol"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"PointerWrapper","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Consider the following example of a shared variable.  One or more","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"threads can wait for data to be published to the variable and when","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"another thread publishes the data, it can signal one of the waiting"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"threads to wake up to collect the data.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is an example for using GCond to block a thread until a condition"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"is satisfied:","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(C Language Example):"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"C","code":["  gpointer current_data = NULL;","  GMutex data_mutex;","  GCond data_cond;","","  void","  push_data (gpointer data)","  {","    g_mutex_lock (&data_mutex);","    current_data = data;","    g_cond_signal (&data_cond);","    g_mutex_unlock (&data_mutex);","  }","","  gpointer","  pop_data (void)","  {","    gpointer data;","","    g_mutex_lock (&data_mutex);","    while (!current_data)","      g_cond_wait (&data_cond, &data_mutex);","    data = current_data;","    current_data = NULL;","    g_mutex_unlock (&data_mutex);","","    return data;","  }"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Whenever a thread calls "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pop_data()"},{"type":"text","text":" now, it will wait until"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"current_data is non-","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":", i.e. until some other thread"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"has called "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"push_data()"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The example shows that use of a condition variable must always be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"paired with a mutex.  Without the use of a mutex, there would be a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"race between the check of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"current_data"},{"type":"text","text":" by the while loop in"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"pop_data()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and waiting. Specifically, another thread could set","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"current_data"},{"type":"text","text":" after the check, and signal the cond (with nobody"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"waiting on it) before the first thread goes to sleep. "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","type":"reference"},{"text":" is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"specifically useful for its ability to release the mutex and go","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to sleep atomically."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is also important to use the "},{"code":"g_cond_wait()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"g_cond_wait_until()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"functions only inside a loop which checks for the condition to be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"true.  See "},{"code":"g_cond_wait()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for an explanation of why the condition may"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"not be true even after it returns."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" is allocated in static storage then it can be used"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"without initialisation.  Otherwise, you should call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cond_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"on it and ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_cond_clear()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" when done."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" should only be accessed via the g_cond_ functions."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol","isActive":true},{"text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GCond"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" as a lighweight, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol"},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/CondProtocol/init_()":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Initialises a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" so that it can be used."}],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"init_"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"title":"init_()","type":"topic","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol\/init_()","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/condprotocol\/init_()"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib","kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","abstract":[],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","role":"collection"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/CondProtocol/timedWait(mutex:absTime:)":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"timedWait","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"MutexT","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"TimeValT"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"mutex","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"MutexT"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"absTime"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"TimeValT"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Waits until this thread is woken up on "},{"code":"cond","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", but not longer than","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"until the time specified by "},{"code":"absTime","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". The "},{"code":"mutex","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is unlocked before"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"falling asleep and locked again before resuming."}],"title":"timedWait(mutex:absTime:)","role":"symbol","deprecated":true,"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/condprotocol\/timedwait(mutex:abstime:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol\/timedWait(mutex:absTime:)"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/CondProtocol/broadcast()":{"abstract":[{"text":"If threads are waiting for ","type":"text"},{"code":"cond","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", all of them are unblocked.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"If no threads are waiting for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cond"},{"text":", this function has no effect.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It is good practice to lock the same mutex as the waiting threads"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"while calling this function, though not required.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"broadcast"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"title":"broadcast()","type":"topic","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol\/broadcast()","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/condprotocol\/broadcast()"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/CondRef":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondRef","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"CondRef"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/condref","kind":"symbol","title":"CondRef","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"CondRef","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":